What you need to know:

High altitude Kapchorwa region in Uganda has churned out prolific athletes such as multiple record holder Cheptegei and ex-Olympics marathon champion KiprotichAt only 20, Uganda’s Jacob Kiplimo is fast becoming a thorn in the flesh for Kenyan athletes, he is the holder of the junior men’s World Cross Country crown and is also the World Half Marathon champion. His coach tips him to go placesThe fast-rising Kiplimo has been giving Kenyan athletes sleepless nights, and his opponents usually refer to him as tough